An interesting point is also gender bias: The gender property of \ourkb{} contains 15K female versus 8K male values. For first names, male ones are still more than female (47% vs. 37% based on the gender-guesser 0.4.0 Python library), but this is still a much lower bias than in other KBs, likely reflecting efforts of gender debiasing the LLM.